title: Family Guy
plot: After drinking too much at a stag party and falling asleep at work, Peter loses his job, signs up for welfare, and gets more money than expected.

title: Death Has a Shadow
plot: Peter tries to smooth things over with Lois after he "innocently" defrauds the government out of hundreds of thousands of dollars.

title: I Never Met the Dead Man
plot: Peter goes into shock, after he disabled the entire Quahog cable system while giving Meg driving lessons; Stewie plots to rid the world of broccoli.
episode_title: I Never Met the Dead Man

title: Chitty Chitty Death Bang
plot: Peter tries to make the best of a bad situation after he ruins Lois' plans for Stewie's birthday party; Meg'a new friend tries to recruit her into a cult.

title: Mind Over Murder
plot: Under house arrest, Peter transforms the basement into a bar, where Lois' singing becomes the main attraction.

title: A Hero Sits Next Door
plot: Peter becomes very jealous, when his handi-capable new neighbor turns out to be the new star player on the toy company's softball team.

title: The Son Also Draws
plot: A chance encounter with a prune smoothie puts in motion a series of events that ultimately allows Peter to accept Chris' artistic side.

title: Brian: Portrait of a Dog
plot: Brian's life is on the line after he refuses to be treated like a dog.

title: Peter, Peter, Caviar Eater
plot: Peter changes for the worse after he and Lois inherit a mansion in Newport.

title: Holy Crap
plot: Peter seeks divine inspiration, when his retired father comes to visit and makes life troublesome; Chris suffers a gastrointestinal impasse.

title: Da Boom
plot: Peter's paranoia about the end of the world makes the family cancel their New Year's Eve '99 plans, but for once, Peter is actually somewhat right.

title: Brian in Love
plot: Brian turns to a therapist after his unrequited love for Lois causes him to lose control of his bladder.

title: Love Thy Trophy
plot: Everyone on Spooner Street becomes enemies when a trophy they all won mysteriously goes missing; Meg makes extra tips as a waitress by telling everyone she's Stewie's teenage mother.

title: Death Is a Bitch
plot: Death pays a visit to the Griffins after Peter fakes his death on an insurance form to avoid paying a hefty hospital bill.

title: The King Is Dead
plot: Lois becomes the director of the Quahog Player's Theatre, until Peter becomes producer and changes everything.

title: I Am Peter, Hear Me Roar
plot: Peter receives feminine training at a woman's retreat after his joke about women offends a female co-worker.
episode_title: I Am Peter, Hear Me Roar

title: If I'm Dyin' I'm Lyin'
plot: Peter pretends Chris is dying so that Make-A-Dream-Come-True foundation can save a cancelled TV Show.

title: Running Mates
plot: Peter resorts to mudslinging, when he and Lois run as opponents in an election for the school board; Chris has a sexual awakening.

title: A Picture Is Worth 1,000 Bucks
plot: Chris becomes the toast of the New York art scene, after Peter uses one his painting as the car's window.

title: Fifteen Minutes of Shame
plot: A vivacious actress will replace Meg, when a reality show based on the Griffins' home life becomes a ratings sensation in the MTV network.

title: Road to Rhode Island
plot: Brian will revisit his childhood home, while he is on an adventurous musical journey from California back to Rhode Island with Stewie.

title: Let's Go to the Hop
plot: Peter infiltrates the high school after it's gripped by a toad-licking craze.

title: Dammit Janet
plot: Stevie falls madly in love with another toddler at his new daycare; Peter takes advantage of Lois' new career as a stewardess.

title: There's Something About Paulie
plot: The mob puts a hit out on Lois, after her meddling puts an end to Peter's unwanted friendship with a crime lord's obnoxious nephew.

title: He's Too Sexy for His Fat
plot: Peter's drastic plastic surgery and liposuction procedures will transform him from a fatherly slob into a beautiful snob, and the family is not sure what to do.
episode_title: He's Too Sexy for His Fat

title: E. Peterbus Unum
plot: A zoning malfunction committed by the city planners gives Peter the opportunity to convert the Griffin household in the sovereign nation of Petirua.

title: The Story on Page One
plot: Peter substitutes Meg's dreary newspaper article on Mayor Adam West with a steamy exposé that tries to out Hollywood actor Luke Perry.

title: Wasted Talent
plot: Lois learns that Peter is a drunken savant when it comes to playing the piano, after he goes on a drinking binge to win one of Pawtucket Pat's silver scrolls.

title: Fore, Father
plot: Peter tries to teach Chris a lesson in responsibility by getting him a. Job at the local golf course; Brian convinces Stewie he was poisoned by a booster shot.

title: The Thin White Line
plot: Brian becomes a drug-sniffing dog for police to get out of a rut after taking the advice of his therapist, but the cocaine may be more than he can handle.

title: Brian Does Hollywood
plot: When Brian leaves the family for Hollywood with dreams of becoming a screenwriter and director, he winds up directing a porn video.

title: Mr. Griffin Goes to Washington
plot: After the toy company is taken over by a tobacco company, Peter is set up as the president and is sent to Washington to lobby against a bill.

title: One If by Clam, Two If by Sea
plot: When a hurricane destroys The Drunken Clam, it is bought by a British man who turns it into an English pub to the dismay of Peter and the gang.
episode_title: One If by Clam, Two If by Sea

title: And the Wiener Is...
plot: Peter becomes jealous of Chris' very large endowment.

title: Death Lives
plot: Peter dies again, and Death shows him the errors of his ways.

title: Lethal Weapons
plot: Lois takes Tae-Jitsu, quickly becomes a black-belt and scares away all of the frustrating New Yorkers that had come to Quahog to view the leaves.

title: The Kiss Seen Round the World
plot: Meg takes an internship to work for Tom with Neil as her partner and kisses him during a life-threading situation that is caught on tape.
episode_title: The Kiss Seen Round the World

title: Mr. Saturday Knight
plot: Losing his job at the toy factory is he least of his concerns, when Peter is caught monkeying around with a renaissance fair wench.

title: A Fish Out of Water
plot: Peter tries to pay of the debts he accrued while pursuing his dream of owning a commercial fishing boat by catching an infamous, man-eating fish.

title: Emission Impossible
plot: After Peter helps deliver Lois's sister's baby, he and Lois decide to try to have another kid, but Stevie will attempt to foil their new plan.

title: To Love and Die in Dixie
plot: After Chris witnesses a convenience store robbery, the Griffins are put in the witness protection program and relocated to the Deep South.
episode_title: To Love and Die in Dixie

title: Screwed the Pooch
plot: Brian confesses to Peter and Lois that he has had sexual yearnings lately, so Lois suggests that Brian join them for a change of scenery.

title: Peter Griffin: Husband, Father... Brother?
plot: While learning about his family history, Chris discovers that one of Peter's ancestors was a black slave once owned by the Pewterschmidts.

title: Ready, Willing and Disabled
plot: Joe becomes a media darling, after Peter spikes his sports drink with steroids during track and field vent for the disabled; the kids bicker over $26.

title: A Very Special Family Guy Freakin' Christmas
plot: Holiday mishaps include Lois going ballistic after losing her Christmas cheer and Peter not being able to watch the KISS Christmas special.
episode_title: A Very Special Family Guy Freakin' Christmas

title: Brian Wallows and Peter's Swallows
plot: Brian is sentenced to community service following a drunk driving episode; Peter cares for three endangered nestlings living in his freshly-grown beard.

title: From Method to Madness
plot: When Brian shows interest in theatre, Lois convinces him to try out for School of Performing Arts, but during the audition, Brian is dismissed by the judges.

title: Stuck Together, Torn Apart
plot: Peter's jealously reaches its peak when going with Lois to the gynecologist, who prepares to examine Lois, but Peter refuses to let him near her.

title: Road to Europe
plot: Stevie and Brian go on a Pan-European journey home after coming stranded in Saudi Arabia; Peter is aghast to learn Lois is not really a fan of KISS.

title: Family Guy Viewer Mail #1
plot: Peter gets three wishes by a genie; The Griffins get superpowers; Quahog turns into the Little Rascals.

title: When You Wish Upon a Weinstein
plot: Driven by his tilted views on Judaism, Peter goes from finding a Jewish accountant to throwing Chris a Bar Mitzvah to make him smart. Meanwhile, a group of angry Catholics are trying to hunt down Peter.
episode_title: When You Wish Upon a Weinstein

title: North by North Quahog
plot: Peter and Lois try for a second honeymoon, but things go awry when he poses as Mel Gibson.

title: Fast Times at Buddy Cianci Jr. High
plot: Chris gets seduced by his new homicidal English teacher; Brian becomes a substitute teacher to a class of thugs.
episode_title: Fast Times at Buddy Cianci Jr. High

title: Blind Ambition
plot: Peter's desire to become famous for something causes him to go blind.

title: Don't Make Me Over
plot: After a makeover, Meg becomes an insufferable starlet.

title: The Cleveland-Loretta Quagmire
plot: Cleveland's wife Loretta has an affair with Quagmire.

title: Petarded
plot: After winning at the children's edition of trivial pursuit, Peter thinks he's a genius until testing proves that he's actually intellectually disabled.

title: Brian the Bachelor
plot: Brian takes part in "The Bachelorette"; Chris takes advice from his talking pimple.

title: 8 Simple Rules for Buying My Teenage Daughter
plot: Peter resorts to selling Meg in order to pay off his pharmacy tab.
episode_title: 8 Simple Rules for Buying My Teenage Daughter

title: Breaking Out Is Hard to Do
plot: Lois goes to jail after a shoplifting crime spree, but when the family breaks her out, they're forced to live in Asiantown.
episode_title: Breaking Out Is Hard to Do

title: Model Misbehavior
plot: Lois becomes a model, but goes overboard with the glamour life.

title: Peter's Got Woods
plot: Brian tries to rename James Woods High School, but Peter pulls out a surprise weapon.

title: The Perfect Castaway
plot: Peter and the guys get stranded on an island, and after being rescued months later, Peter realizes things aren't what they used to be.

title: Jungle Love
plot: To avoid Freshman hazing, Chris runs away to South America, when the family get him, Peter learns that he's the richest man in the tribe.

title: PTV
plot: After an incident at the Emmys, the FCC overreacts, so Peter decides to start his own cable network, until the FCC shut him down and start censoring his life.

title: Brian Goes Back to College
plot: Brian re-enrolls at Brown while Peter and the guys become the new A-Team.

title: The Courtship of Stewie's Father
plot: Peter tries to bond with Stewie in a number of different ways.

title: Fat Guy Strangler
plot: Lois discovers a long-lost brother, but her new relative has a deadly secret.

title: The Father, the Son and the Holy Fonz
plot: During one of his visits Peter's father, Francis, discovers that Stewie has never been baptized, so without Lois' permission Peter and Francis go to church and have him baptized. Upon discovering this, Lois convinces Peter that Stewie should have been able to worship whomever he wanted regardless of his father's religion. Naturally Peter interprets Lois' wisdom the wrong way so decides to start his own religious group that praises the television character, Arthur "Fonzie" Fonzarelli.
episode_title: The Father, the Son and the Holy Fonz

title: Brian Sings and Swings
plot: Brian and Stewie go on tour singing classic tunes with Frank Sinatra, Jr.

title: Patriot Games
plot: After quarterback Tom Brady witnesses Peter pummeling several people in order to get to the bathroom, he recruits him to play for the New England Patriots.

title: I Take Thee, Quagmire
plot: Quagmire falls in love with and marries the maid that Peter won on a game show only to find out that she's a psycho and must figure out a way to get out of it.

title: Sibling Rivalry
plot: Peter reluctantly agrees to get a vasectomy, and refuses to have sex, causing Lois to gain weight; Stewie's half-brother Bertram declare an all-out war for control over the playground.

title: Deep Throats
plot: While Meg interns for Mayor West, Brian uncovers a scandal; Peter and Lois decide to reunite their old groovy band

title: Peterotica
plot: Peter becomes a best-selling erotica book author. But a lawsuit puts his investor--Lois's father--in the poorhouse and forces him to move in with the Griffins.

title: You May Now Kiss the... Uh... Guy Who Receives
plot: Brian's gay cousin Jasper comes to town to marry his fiancé, until Mayor West bans gay marriage to distract everyone from a financial scandal.
episode_title: You May Now Kiss the... Uh... Guy Who Receives

title: Petergeist
plot: Peter's attempt to open build a movie theater on the Indian burial ground in his backyard releases a poltergeist that sucks Stevie into the television set.

title: The Griffin Family History
plot: When burglars break into the house, the Griffins take cover in the attic, where Peter tells them about their family history.

title: Stewie B. Goode
plot: A near-death experience inspires Stewie to change his life.

title: Bango Was His Name-O
plot: Stewie searches a man he saw on TV whom he believes is his real father.

title: Stu & Stewie's Excellent Adventure
plot: Stewie meets his future self, who lives a pathetic life.

title: Stewie Loves Lois
plot: After she saves Rupert, Stewie smothers Lois with affection; After his first prostate exam, Peter sues Dr. Hartman for sexual harassment.

title: Mother Tucker
plot: Peter's mom starts dating Tom Tucker; Brian and Stewie begin hosting their own raunchy radio program.

title: Hell Comes to Quahog
plot: Meg takes a job at a new superstore, which causes Peter to lose his job and the town's electricity.

title: Saving Private Brian
plot: Stewie and Brian join the army and are sent to Iraq; Chris becomes the lead singer of a rock band.

title: Whistle While Your Wife Works
plot: Lois does Peter's work at the brewery while he recovers from getting his fingers surgically reattached, and Brian doesn't want the family to know that he's dating an idiot.

title: Prick Up Your Ears
plot: Lois becomes the high school sex ed teacher, but is fired for having "radical" views. So she is replaced by a Christian group that uses fear, misinformation and lies to promote abstinence.

title: Chick Cancer
plot: Stewie tries to win over a retired child actress, and Peter becomes a fan of "chick movies" and makes his own.

title: Barely Legal
plot: After taking her to the prom, Meg becomes obsessed with Brian; Peter, Cleveland and Quagmire join the police force to help Joe.

title: Road to Rupert
plot: Brian and Stewie travel to Aspen after Brian accidentally sells Rupert at a yard sale. Meanwhile, Peter loses his license and Meg becomes his driver.

title: Peter's Two Dads
plot: After Francis dies, Peter learns his real biological father lives in Ireland, so he and Brian set out to find him.

title: The Tan Aquatic with Steve Zissou
plot: Peter becomes the neighborhood bully after trying to take care of Chris's bully, and Stewie has a cancer scare after staying in the tanning bed too long.
episode_title: The Tan Aquatic with Steve Zissou

title: Airport '07
plot: Peter becomes a redneck and gets Quagmire fired. So the gang sets out to get Quagmire his job back.

title: Bill & Peter's Bogus Journey
plot: Peter's attempts to become physically fit lead to a friendship with Bill Clinton, which inadvertently nearly destroys Peter & Lois' marriage.

title: No Meals on Wheels
plot: After Peter finds a valuable coin and sells it for $50,000, he opens his own restaurant, but things don't end well when he bans Joe and all of his handicapped friends.

title: Boys Do Cry
plot: Lois gets a job as the church organist, so the family decides to begin going back to church. When Stewie gets sick after receiving communion, the congregation becomes convinced that he has been possessed by the devil. While on the run, the family ends up in Texas, where Peter begins to fit right in with the cowboys, Stewie enters the "Little Miss Texas" pageant, and Chris and Meg sneak into George W. Bush's house.

title: No Chris Left Behind
plot: After being expelled for having the lowest average standardized test score, Chris is accepted into a snobby private school, forcing the family to struggle to pay the tuition.

title: It Takes a Village Idiot, and I Married One
plot: Lois runs for mayor of Quahog, though she doesn't become the front-runner until she dumbs down her political views. Once in office, she becomes corrupted with the power that she now holds, and begins accepting bribes so that she can buy herself expensive things. Meanwhile, Peter comes to enjoy being the "first lady" of Quahog, and all of the perks that go along with it.
episode_title: It Takes a Village Idiot, and I Married One

title: Meet the Quagmires
plot: Death grants Peter's wish to go back in time to 1984 to be 18 again, but when he bails on Lois, he soon learns he's alters the present, where Lois is married to Quagmire.

title: Blue Harvest
plot: With the Griffins stuck at home during a blackout, Peter tells the story of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope.

title: Movin' Out (Brian's Song)
plot: Brian moves in with Jillian, but Stewie moves in to to help pay the rent. Meg and Chris both get jobs at the local convenience store.

title: Believe It or Not, Joe's Walking on Air
plot: Joe has a new surgery performed on him which allows him to walk. But the new Joe then abandons all of his old friends because they're all a bunch of lazy losers.
episode_title: Believe It or Not, Joe's Walking on Air

title: Stewie Kills Lois
plot: Stewie kills his mother Lois. But one year after her disappearance, Peter is charged with her death.

title: Lois Kills Stewie
plot: With Lois back in Quahog, Stewie escapes with Brian to Washington, D.C. and sets out to initiate his latest plan for world domination.

title: Padre de Familia
plot: Peter discovers that he is an illegal Mexican immigrant, so he is forced to take a job as a day laborer for Lois's father.

title: Peter's Daughter
plot: Meg is admitted to hospital due to a severe accident, and Peter vows to treat her better than he ever has before.

title: McStroke
plot: Peter sues a fast food chain after he suffers a stroke from eating over 30 hamburgers in one sitting.

title: Back to the Woods
plot: James Woods gets his revenge on Peter by stealing his identity and moving in with his family. Peter responds by stealing Woods' identity and ruining his career.

title: Play It Again, Brian
plot: Brian decides to declare his love for Lois as she and Peter accompany him to a writers' convention, and the Griffin kids are babysat by Herbert.

title: The Former Life of Brian
plot: When Brian decides to look up an old flame on a whim, he discovers, to his horror, that he is the father of her teenage son.

title: Long John Peter
plot: Peter begins to live like a pirate when he gets a pet parrot. He terrorizes his neighbors and creates havoc in Quahog. When Chris takes Brian to the vet, Chris falls in love with the lovely intern Anna.

title: Love Blactually
plot: Stewie convinces Brian to take it slow with his new girlfriend, but she becomes impatient and hooks up with Cleveland. Brian then tries to get Cleveland back together with his ex-wife Loretta to get him out of the picture.

title: I Dream of Jesus
plot: Peter discovers that Jesus Christ is working at a used record store in Quahog, and sets out to let everyone know that he has come back.

title: Road to Germany
plot: Stewie and Brian use a time machine to go back to Nazi-era Poland and rescue Mort.

title: Baby Not on Board
plot: The Griffins decide to take a vacation to the Grand Canyon, only to leave Stewie behind.

title: The Man with Two Brians
plot: Peter gets the Griffins a new, younger dog to eventually replace an aging Brian.

title: Tales of a Third Grade Nothing
plot: Peter must pass the third grade in order to get a promotion at the brewery. Brian and Frank Sinatra Jr. buy the nightclub, and Stewie turns it into a trendy hotspot.
episode_title: Tales of a Third Grade Nothing

title: Ocean's Three and a Half
plot: The guys try to find a way to help Joe and Bonnie get money to pay their hospital bills after their baby is born, a baby that Stewie has a crush on

title: Family Gay
plot: Peter becomes temporarily gay after participating in a medical study.

title: The Juice Is Loose!
plot: Everyone is up in arms after Peter becomes friends with O.J. Simpson.

title: FOX-y Lady
plot: Lois gets a job as an anchor at Fox News, while Peter and Chris try to sell a cartoon pilot to the Fox network.

title: Not All Dogs Go to Heaven
plot: Meg becomes religious and tries to convert Brian from Atheism; Stewie teleports the cast of Star Trek: The Next Generation to Quahog.
episode_title: Not All Dogs Go to Heaven

plot: Brian becomes the leading proponent for legalization of marijuana in Quahog.

title: Stew-Roids
plot: Stewie begins taking steroids after he is beat up by Susie. Meanwhile, Chris begins dating one of the most popular girls in the school.

title: We Love You Conrad
plot: Brian dates "Hills" star Lauren Conrad while trying to hide the fact that he is in love with someone else.

title: Three Kings
plot: A series of parodies based on the Stephen King movies "Stand by Me," "Misery," and "The Shawshank Redemption."

title: Peter's Progress
plot: The story of Griffin Peterson and the founding of Quahog.

title: Road to the Multiverse
plot: Brian and Stewie explore a series of alternate universes.

title: Family Goy
plot: When Lois finds out her mother was a Holocaust survivor, Peter decides to adopt the Jewish faith.

title: Spies Reminiscent of Us
plot: With the help of Chevy Chase and Dan Aykroyd, Stewie and Brian discover that Mayor West is a Cold War sleeper agent; Peter, Quagmire, and Joe start an improv group.

title: Brian's Got a Brand New Bag
plot: When Brian snags an older woman, he becomes the laughingstock of the family, but things go from bad to worse when she breaks her hip and Brian has to be her errand-boy.
episode_title: Brian's Got a Brand New Bag

title: Hannah Banana
plot: Brian helps Stewie meet Miley Cyrus before her concert in Quahog, and they discover a secret about her identity. Meanwhile, the family discovers that the evil monkey in Chris's closet isn't actually evil.

title: Quagmire's Baby
plot: Quagmire is forced to take care of a baby he fathered when she is left on his doorstep, while Stewie creates clones of himself and Brian.

title: Jerome Is the New Black
plot: The guys find a new black friend to join their group, until Peter finds out that he slept with Lois. Meanwhile, Brian tries to find out why Quagmire hates him and tries to make amends.

title: Dog Gone
plot: When Brian accidentally kills another dog, and is surprised when no one cares, he tries to convince everyone that a dog's life should have the same value as a human.

title: Business Guy
plot: Peter takes over Pewterschmidt Industries when Carter has a heart attack and goes into a coma.

title: Big Man on Hippocampus
plot: The Griffins are invited to be contestants on the game show "Family Feud." After winning the game and advancing to the show's bonus round (called Fast Money), Lois puts the Griffins in prime position to win the game, but Peter bungles the opportunity when he stubbornly refuses to change his answer to the first question. Host Richard Dawson tries to remind Peter of the rules, but when Peter continues to argue and grabs Dawson, he gets pushed through a podium on the set and is knocked unconscious. At the hospital, Dr. Hartman tells Lois that Peter has amnesia. At home, ...

title: Dial Meg for Murder
plot: Meg goes to prison after her boyfriend escapes from jail, and returns as a frightening, hardened sociopath.

title: Extra Large Medium
plot: After they are saved after being lost in the wilderness, Stewie helps Chris muster up the courage to ask a girl with Down Syndrome out on a date, while Peter pretends to be a psychic.

title: Go, Stewie, Go!
plot: Stewie poses as a girl so that he can appear on Jolly Farm, and falls for a female co-star; Peter makes Lois feel bad about her age.

title: Peter-assment
plot: Peter is sexually harassed by Angela, but will he follow through with her advances and keep his job?

title: Brian Griffin's House of Payne
plot: Brian sells his pilot for a heartwarming family drama to CBS, who turns it into a sitcom starring James Woods; Meg and Chris try to hide Stewie's accidental injury, which they caused.

title: April in Quahog
plot: Peter makes an embarrassing confession about his kids as everyone thinks the world is about to come to an end.

title: Brian & Stewie
plot: Brian and Stewie get locked in a bank vault where they are forced to deal with each other on a whole new level.

title: Quagmire's Dad
plot: Quagmire's dad visits and announces he's undergoing a sex change; Brian returns to town after a seminar, and ends up sleeping with Quagmire's dad after the sex change.

title: The Splendid Source
plot: With Cleveland's help, Peter, Joe and Quagmire blow off a couples getaway to Maine to search for the origin of the worlds funniest dirty joke.

title: Something, Something, Something, Dark Side
plot: Peter makes good on another power outage at home by retelling Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back.

title: Partial Terms of Endearment
plot: Lois agrees to become a surrogate mother for a friend who is unable to conceive a child of her own. But when the friend and her husband are killed in a car accident, Lois and Peter consider whether to terminate the pregnancy.

title: And Then There Were Fewer
plot: The residents of Quahog are invited to James Woods' house, where a murder mystery takes place.

title: Excellence in Broadcasting
plot: Brian does a 180 on Rush Limbaugh and befriends him after he reads one of his books.

title: Welcome Back Carter
plot: After Peter catches Carter having an affair, he is strong-armed into keeping a secret, until he accidentally spills the beans.

title: Halloween on Spooner Street
plot: Peter and Joe team up to execute Halloween pranks on Quagmire; Brian shows Stewie the ropes of trick-or-treating; Meg sets out to attend her first high school Halloween party.

title: Baby, You Knock Me Out
plot: Lois becomes a champion foxy boxer, and Peter acts as her manager.

title: Brian Writes a Bestseller
plot: Feeling discouraged with the progress of his writing career, Brian decides to throw in the towel until Stewie becomes his manager and one of his books hits the bestseller list. But when the fame goes to his head, Brian gets a wake-up call from Bill Maher. Meanwhile, Lois decides that she and Peter need separate beds, a decision that leaves Peter looking for a new cuddle buddy.

title: Road to the North Pole
plot: Disappointed with the Mall Santa, Stewie and Brian decide to go up to the North Pole to teach Santa a lesson, only to face a shocking revelation.

title: New Kidney in Town
plot: Peter needs a new kidney after he destroys his making his own Red Bull; Chris gets to introduce President Obama after plagiarising Meg's poem.

title: And I'm Joyce Kinney
plot: Lois becomes friends with the new news anchor, only to have her reveal Lois's most embarrassing secret on air.

title: Friends of Peter G.
plot: After a public disturbance, Peter and Brian are forced to attend a 12-step meeting to help kick their drinking problems. Unable to recognize his issue, Peter gets a visit from Death, who gives him a glimpse of what life would be like with and without "Mr. Booze" in his bloodstream.

title: German Guy
plot: A jealous Mr. Herbert tries to tell Chris that the elderly German puppeteer that he is hanging out with is actually a notorious Nazi war criminal.

title: The Hand That Rocks the Wheelchair
plot: Meg takes care of Joe while Bonnie is away, and develops a crush; Stewie creates an evil clone who escapes the house.
episode_title: The Hand That Rocks the Wheelchair

title: Trading Places
plot: Chris and Meg think their parents have it easy, and Peter and Lois beg to differ, so in order to teach them a lesson, they all trade roles. Chris goes to work at the brewery while Meg runs the house. While things start off well, it's not long until the stress of running a household and being the sole breadwinner break down Chris and Meg.

title: Tiegs for Two
plot: When the local dry cleaner loses Peter's favorite white shirt, he goes ballistic. Meanwhile, Brian tries to score on a date with a new friend, Denise, but ends up striking out. Instead of calling it quits on love, he decides to enlist Quagmire's help, but things get nasty when they start to compete for the affections of each other's old flames, Cheryl Tiegs and Jillian.

title: Brothers & Sisters
plot: Lois's sister comes to town after yet another failed marriage, and quickly becomes engaged to mayor Adam West.

title: The Big Bang Theory
plot: Stewie and Brian go back in time to stop Bertram from killing Leonardo da Vinci.

title: Foreign Affairs
plot: Lois goes on a vacation with Bonnie to Paris, unaware of her intentions; Peter homeschools Chris and Meg.

title: Episode VI: It's a Trap
plot: The Griffins reprise their intergalactic roles in an outrageous retelling of Return of the Jedi.

title: Lottery Fever
plot: When the Griffins win millions in the lottery, they can't handle the good fortune and struggle to stay grounded.

title: Seahorse Seashell Party
plot: As a hurricane hits Quahog, Brian gets high on mushrooms; Meg finally summons up the courage to confront the family.

title: Screams of Silence: The Story of Brenda Q
plot: Quagmire and the guys try to save his sister Brenda from her abusive boyfriend.
episode_title: Screams of Silence: The Story of Brenda Q

title: Stewie Goes for a Drive
plot: Stewie runs away after crashing Brian's car; Peter befriends Ryan Reynolds.

title: Back to the Pilot
plot: Brian and Stewie travel back in time to January 31, 1999 to change history, only to alter the past with dire consequences.

title: Thanksgiving
plot: Joe's son, who was reported missing in Iraq, suddenly and unexpectedly appears during Thanksgiving dinner, but the story of his disappearance doesn't add up.

title: Amish Guy
plot: The Griffins stay in an Amish village after their car breaks down, but problems arise when Meg falls for a boy in the village.

title: Cool Hand Peter
plot: Peter and the guys take a stand against their wives and flee to the Deep South on a road trip, only to earn a one-way ticket to jail.

title: Grumpy Old Man
plot: Lois's dad retires to a senior community in Florida, but has trouble getting used to it.

title: Meg and Quagmire
plot: When Meg turns 18, Quagmire tries to make his move on her, but Peter tries to stop him.

title: The Blind Side
plot: Brian dates a blind woman who hates dogs; Peter can't stop falling down the new stairs.

title: Livin' on a Prayer
plot: When Lois discovers that Stewie's sick playmate is being denied medical treatment because his parents are Christian Scientists, she decides to take matters into her own hands.

title: Tom Tucker: The Man and His Dream
plot: Tom Tucker revives his acting career, with Peter as his agent; Chris starts dating a girl who looks exactly like Lois.
episode_title: Tom Tucker: The Man and His Dream

title: Be Careful What You Fish For
plot: Peter allows a friendly dolphin to move in with the family, but soon discovers that he's really a jerk. Meanwhile, Stewie asks for Brian's help in busting a negligent day care provider.
episode_title: Be Careful What You Fish For

title: Burning Down the Bayit
plot: Mort, Peter and Quagmire burn down Goldman's pharmacy to collect the insurance money, but things go awry when Joe starts to look into the case.

title: Killer Queen
plot: Peter and Chris are sent to fat camp, where a serial killer targets overweight kids; Stewie is traumatized by the frightening Queen album cover.

title: Forget-Me-Not
plot: After a car accident, Peter, Brian, Joe, and Quagmire wake up in a hospital with no memory and discover that they're the last people left on Earth.

title: You Can't Do That on Television, Peter
plot: Peter creates his own children's TV show, portraying Lois as an annoying nag; Meg shadows Dr. Hartman.
episode_title: You Can't Do That on Television, Peter

title: Mr. & Mrs. Stewie
plot: Stewie falls for a girl who's just as wicked as him; Peter and Quagmire take their friendship to the next level.

title: Leggo My Meg-O
plot: Meg and her friend are kidnapped in Paris for the sex slave trade, and Stewie and Brian fly to Paris to rescue her.

title: Tea Peter
plot: Peter joins the Tea Party but doesn't discover until it's too late that Carter Pewterschmidt is using the party to get rid of government for his own selfish motives.

title: Viewer Mail #2
plot: A British version of Family Guy; Everybody Peter touches turns into Robin Williams; A day through Stewie's point of view.

title: Internal Affairs
plot: Peter talks Joe into having an affair with his new attractive partner, until Bonnie finds out.

title: Into Fat Air
plot: The Griffins try to beat Lois's obnoxious ex-boyfriend's family to the top of Mount Everest.

title: Ratings Guy
plot: After the Griffins become a Nielsen Family, everyone gets mad at Peter for convincing the networks to make ridiculous changes to popular shows.

title: The Old Man and the Big 'C'
plot: Brian and Stewie learn that Carter Pewterschmidt's company has developed a cure for cancer, but is keeping it from the public.
episode_title: The Old Man and the Big 'C'

title: Yug Ylimaf
plot: Brian causes time to move backwards when he tampers with Stewie's time machine, which may result in Stewie being unborn.

title: Joe's Revenge
plot: Joe, with the help of Peter and Quagmire, looks to track down the person responsible for his injuries.

title: Lois Comes Out of Her Shell
plot: Lois goes through a mid-life crisis; Stewie discovers that his new pet turtle is evil.
episode_title: Lois Comes Out of Her Shell

title: Friends Without Benefits
plot: Meg finds out that her crush is actually gay and is interested in Chris.

title: Jesus, Mary and Joseph!
plot: The Griffins decorate their tree while Peter tells the story of Christmas.

title: Space Cadet
plot: The Griffins wind up stuck in orbit on a space shuttle after Peter and Lois send Chris to Florida for space camp.

title: Brian's Play
plot: Brian receives widespread acclaim for his new play, until Stewie writes one overnight that puts his to shame.

title: The Giggity Wife
plot: After a drunken night out at Harvard with the guys, Quagmire discovers that he married a decrepit old prostitute.

title: Valentine's Day in Quahog
plot: Shows how the individual characters spend their Valentine's Day.

title: Chris Cross
plot: Chris is fed up with Meg blackmailing him, so he moves in with Mr. Herbert; Stewie and Brian become huge fans of Anne Murray.

title: Call Girl
plot: Lois works for a phone sex line and Peter falls in love with her, not knowing that he is actually speaking to his wife.

title: Turban Cowboy
plot: Peter becomes a Muslim but later discovers that he is also part of a terrorist plot to blow up a bridge in Quahog.

title: 12 and a Half Angry Men
plot: Mayor West is on trial for murder, and Brian is the only one on the jury who thinks he is not guilty.

title: Bigfat
plot: Peter reverts back to a feral state after being lost in the Canadian wilderness for two months after a plane crash.

title: Total Recall
plot: Stewie tries to rescue Rupert after he is recalled; Lois hangs out with Joe and Quagmire while Peter is sick.

title: Save the Clam
plot: The guys fight to save The Drunken Clam from closing after Horace dies; Meg gets a job at a funeral home.

title: Farmer Guy
plot: Due to the high crime rate in Quaghog, the family move to a farm, where they discover a meth lab in the basement.

title: Roads to Vegas
plot: Stewie's teleportation device malfunctions when he and Brian use it to travel to Las Vegas.

title: No Country Club for Old Men
plot: The Griffins are introduced to the Country Club lifestyle when Chris begins dating the owner's daughter, much to the chagrin of Carter.
episode_title: No Country Club for Old Men

title: Finders Keepers
plot: Peter goes on a real-life treasure hunt based on a treasure map from a child's meal menu.

title: Vestigial Peter
plot: Peter has a vestigial twin growing of his neck, and he has surgery to remove it and have it become a separate entity.

title: Quagmire's Quagmire
plot: Quagmire falls in love with a woman who is just as kinky as he is, but doesn't find out until it's too late that she's a complete psycho.

title: A Fistful of Meg
plot: Meg turns to Quagmire for help taking on a school bully, and Brian looks for a way to get back at Peter for forcing him to see him naked.

title: Boopa-dee Bappa-dee
plot: The Griffins take a trip to Italy and are forced to deal with annoying immigration laws after Peter destroys the family's passports.

title: Life of Brian
plot: Brian dies and Stewie cannot use his time machine to save him. Meanwhile, Peter replaces Brian with an Italian dog named Vinny.

title: Into Harmony's Way
plot: Fame gets to Peter when he forms a song writing team with Quagmire.

title: Christmas Guy
plot: Peter fills Carter with the spirit of Christmas. Meanwhile, Stewie goes back in time to save Brian.

title: Peter Problems
plot: Lately Peter hasn't been able to perform very well in the bedroom. So he asks Quagmire and Joe to step in and help him get his mojo back.

title: Grimm Job
plot: Peter tells Stewie the stories "Jack and the Beanstalk," "Little Red Riding Hood," and "Cinderella."

title: Brian's a Bad Father
plot: Brian uses his son to get a writing job for a TV show, and Quagmire stops being friends with Peter after Peter shoots him.

title: Mom's the Word
plot: Peter is seduced by his late mother's longtime friend, while Stewie is distraught over the realities of death.

title: 3 Acts of God
plot: Peter is sick of opposing football teams thanking God for beating the Patriots, so he and the guys go on a quest to find the Lord and ask Him to stop interfering in the outcomes of football games.

title: Fresh Heir
plot: When Chris is made the sole future heir to Carter's fortune after caring for him, Peter takes drastic measures to keep the wealth within his reach - by marrying Chris.

title: Secondhand Spoke
plot: Peter is asked to be the face of an anti-smoking campaign after taking up smoking cigarettes, while Stewie helps Chris face school bullies.

title: Herpe, the Love Sore
plot: Stewie gets herpes from Brian, while Peter and the guys discover that another group has taken their favorite booth at the Drunken Clam.

title: The Most Interesting Man in the World
plot: Lois calls Peter an idiot for bringing home the wrong baby, so he goes to Chicago on a business trip and returns a smart, classy person.
episode_title: The Most Interesting Man in the World

title: Baby Got Black
plot: Chris runs away with Jerome's daughter Pam, whom Jerome has forbidden Chris from dating, so Jerome must work with Peter to find their kids.

title: Meg Stinks!
plot: Peter takes Meg to a college for an interview, but end up partying; Brian is forced to live outside after being sprayed by a skunk.

title: He's Bla-ack!
plot: Cleveland returns to Quahog, but is forbidden from spending time with Peter when their wives get into an argument over parenting.

title: Chap Stewie
plot: Stewie tries to erase himself from history when Peter and Chris constantly interrupt his TV time, only to end up as the baby of a British family.

title: The Simpsons Guy
plot: After fleeing Quahog due to Peter's misogynistic comic strip, the Griffins get their car stolen and end up getting stuck in Springfield.

title: The Book of Joe
plot: Peter is hired to read Joe's new children's book; Brian takes up running to impress a girl.

title: Baking Bad
plot: Peter and Lois open a bakery, but things get out of hand when Peter comes up with a way to attract customers.

title: Brian the Closer
plot: After getting a cosmetic surgery, Brian becomes a real estate agent, only to get in trouble with Quagmire.

title: Turkey Guys
plot: On the night before Thanksgiving, Peter and Brian get drunk and eat the whole turkey, so they have to get a new one on Thanksgiving Day. With Peter gone, Stewie tries to help Chris take over as the man of the house.

title: The 2,000-Year-Old Virgin
plot: Peter and the guys set out to throw Jesus the best birthday party in order to help him lose his virginity.

title: Stewie, Chris & Brian's Excellent Adventure
plot: Stewie and Brian take Chris back through time to help him with history class, only to end up stuck in the past.

title: Our Idiot Brian
plot: Brian begins to think he's not so smart when he takes the SAT'S for Meg and gets a low score, so Peter decides to show him the joys of being an idiot.

title: This Little Piggy
plot: Meg becomes a foot-fetish model; Brian accompanies Stewie on an adventure outside of preschool.

title: Quagmire's Mom
plot: Quagmire faces charges of statutory rape. During the trial, his mom makes a surprise appearance, which helps explain why he is the way that he is.

title: Encyclopedia Griffin
plot: Peter and the guys start a detective agency and discover that Chris is a thief. In the meantime, Lois is worried about Chris when gets involved in a delusional relationship.

title: Stewie Is Enceinte
plot: Stewie impregnates himself with Brian's DNA to save their friendship, while Peter and the guys try to make a viral video.

title: Dr. C and the Women
plot: Cleveland becomes an unlicensed therapist and gives Lois marriage advice that Peter does not like, and Quagmire gets Meg a job working in airport security.

title: #JOLO
plot: Joe decides to embrace life by quitting his job with the police and taking the guys on a road trip to Niagra Falls, where he makes an unexpected decision.

title: Once Bitten
plot: Brian becomes more submissive as a result of attending obedience school and Chris discovers his new friend is using him to get close to Meg.

title: Roasted Guy
plot: When Peter's insulted by old friends at a roasting of him, he joins a group of mean girls.

title: Fighting Irish
plot: Peter prepares for a fight with Liam Neeson, while Lois becomes a class mom and pays more attention to the other children over Stewie.

title: Take My Wife
plot: Lois books a couple's vacation, but it turns out to be a marriage counseling program. Carter is frustrated because the kids are so into their electronics.

title: Pilling Them Softly
plot: Stewie gets addicted to Adderal; Peter and Quagmire make their own cooking shows which rival each other.

title: Papa Has a Rollin' Son
plot: When Joe learns his father hates handicapped people, Peter pretends to be Joe; Stewie becomes friends with Tom Cruise after learning he will grow up to be only 5'1.

title: Guy, Robot
plot: Stewie builds a robot friend after a fight with Brian and Lois makes Peter buy a new mattress.

title: Peternormal Activity
plot: When the guys go to an abandoned asylum to gain inspiration for a new horror movie, they accidentally kill a man; Annoyed with Brian's perceived pretension, Stewie endeavours to destroy them.

title: Peter, Chris & Brian
plot: After watching a VHS tape of his younger self, Peter, with Brian's help, launch a plan to make sure Chris doesn't take the same path.

title: Peter's Sister
plot: Peter's sister Karen comes over for Thanksgiving, while Stewie goes a little too far as he and Brian go on a cleanse to avoid overeating.

title: Hot Pocket-Dial
plot: Quagmire finally confesses his love for Lois, but it happens while he accidentally pocket dials Peter, who is furious, so Brian tries to fix the situation.

title: Brokeback Swanson
plot: Joe becomes a quadriplegic while Brian has an affair with a married woman.

title: A Shot in the Dark
plot: While participating in a newly formed neighborhood watch group, Peter is arrested and charged with a hate crime.

title: Candy, Quahog Marshmallow
plot: When the guys travel to Korea to retrieve the final episode of an Asian soap that Quagmire starred in, Quagmire is reunited with a former lover.

title: The Peanut Butter Kid
plot: Stewie's new role brings Peter and Lois into show business.

title: Scammed Yankees
plot: Peter and Carter go to Africa to return Carter's money he lost to a Nigerian scammer. Meanwhile, Brian tries to hook up with one of Meg's friends after he finds out that she has a great body.

title: An App a Day
plot: Peter learns about phone apps and overloads his phone with them. He buys a new phone with more memory and gives his old phone to Chris, which causes a series of horrible events. Meanwhile, Stewie joins a tennis club and invites Brian to be his tennis partner.

title: Underage Peter
plot: Peter uses Brian as a way to get alcohol, after Mayor West bans alcohol from all people under 50.

title: A Lot Going on Upstairs
plot: Peter turns the attic into a man cave, which makes Lois furious; Stewie builds a device to enable Brian to help Stewie conquer his terrifying nightmares.

title: The Heartbreak Dog
plot: Brian and Bonnie run away together after declaring their love for each other meanwhile Meg starts volunteer work in a retirement home.

title: Take a Letter
plot: An old flame returns to Peter's life after Lois finds a dead letter at the post office. Stewie goes to a new preschool and tries to fit in with a rich new friend.

title: The New Adventures of Old Tom
plot: Peter gets lost in the mall while Brian pretends to be a millionaire to impress a woman.
episode_title: The New Adventures of Old Tom

title: Run, Chris, Run
plot: Meg discovers that the cool kids only elected Chris homecoming king just to prank him; The guys look for a new black friend when Cleveland starts hanging out with Jerome.

title: Road to India
plot: Brian falls in love with a tech support girl, so he and Stewie go to India to find her; Peter becomes the center of attention when he's invited to Joe's bingo night.

title: The Boys in the Band
plot: Stewie and Brian form a children's band that threatens to fall apart when Olivia gets involved, while Chris gets a job managing Quagmire's sex life.

title: Bookie of the Year
plot: Peter starts betting on Chris when he becomes a pitcher; Brian and Stewie re-team with Frank Sinatra, Jr. to start an Italian restaurant.

title: American Gigg-olo
plot: After the pilots go on strike, Quagmire becomes a gigolo. Meanwhile, Brian works at a hardware store for the health insurance.

title: Inside Family Guy
plot: James Woods leads viewers behind the scenes of the studios of Family Guy.

title: Chris Has Got a Date, Date, Date, Date, Date
plot: Taylor Swift agrees to be Chris' homecoming date, while Peter becomes an Uber driver.
episode_title: Chris Has Got a Date, Date, Date, Date, Date

title: Hot Shots
plot: Lois decides not to vaccinate Stewie to "save" him from autism, causing Stewie to run away, and cause the town to have an outbreak.

title: High School English
plot: The cast reenact three classic novels commonly taught in high school; The Great Gatsby, The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn and Of Mice and Men.

title: Carter and Tricia
plot: Carter falls in love with Channel 5 News reporter, Tricia Takanawa; Stewie becomes Brian's driving instructor.

title: How the Griffin Stole Christmas
plot: Peter fills in for the mall Santa and becomes drunk with power; Stewie and Brian crash holiday parties for free food, drama and women.

title: Passenger Fatty-Seven
plot: Quagmire's piloting skills are questioned when he scores free tickets to a guys' trip to San Francisco, and the plane is hijacked on the flight home.

title: Gronkowsbees
plot: Rob Gronkowski moves in behind the Griffins; Stewie begins beekeeping, and gives them steroids, which makes them aggressive.

title: Peter's Def Jam
plot: When the guys start a podcast, Peter goes solo and becomes a DJ; Lois' allergy forces Brian to move into Stewie's room.

title: The Finer Strings
plot: Peter fails to make the cut when the guys form a string quartet; Brian enjoys the life of luxury too much as Carter's seeing eye dog.

title: The Dating Game
plot: Quagmire discovers Tinder, forcing the guys to intervene. Meanwhile, Stewie learns the perks of scoliosis.

title: Cop and a Half-Wit
plot: Peter helps Joe solve crime cases; Stewie joins a football team, and panics when he gets a concussion.

title: Saturated Fat Guy
plot: When Lois forces him to eat healthy food, Peter opens up his own food truck with fattening foods; Meg joins a roller derby team.

title: Peter's Lost Youth
plot: Peter gets jealous when Lois upstages him at a Red Sox Fantasy Baseball camp; Stewie runs away when Meg babysits him.

title: The Peter Principal
plot: Meg takes advantage of Peter's temporary job as principal to get even with her bullies; Brian and Stewie open a B&B that quickly turns into a brothel.

title: Dearly Deported
plot: Chris volunteers to take care of his Mexican girlfriend's twin babies, but after learning that she can't come back to the U.S, the Griffins go to Mexico.

title: A House Full of Peters
plot: Peter's past participation as a sperm donor catches up to him when his children start showing up at his house.

title: Emmy-Winning Episode
plot: Peter decides to make "Family Guy" more like Emmy-winning shows so it can finally win TV's highest award.

title: Foxx in the Men House
plot: Peter dumps Quagmire, Joe, and Cleveland when he becomes friends with a cool paramedic.

title: Nanny Goats
plot: The Griffins get a nanny for the kids, giving Peter and Lois the opportunity to reconnect.

title: Follow the Money
plot: Chris receives a special one-dollar bill for his birthday that gets passed throughout Quahog.

title: Three Directors
plot: The story of Peter's firing from the brewery, as told in the styles of Quentin Tarantino, Wes Anderson, and Michael Bay.

title: The D in Apartment 23
plot: Brian gets kicked out of the house for posting an offensive tweet that goes viral.

title: Petey IV
plot: Vladimir Putin comes to Quahog after Peter writes to him; A strapped-for-cash Brian gets a job at a suicide hotline.

title: Crimes and Meg's Demeanor
plot: Meg's drinking both concerns and delights Peter; Brian suspects Principal Shepherd of a crime.

title: Don't Be a Dickens at Christmas
plot: Peter is visited by the ghosts of Christmas past, present and future, who take him on a journey around Quahog.
episode_title: Don't Be a Dickens at Christmas

title: Boy (Dog) Meets Girl (Dog)
plot: Brian enters a dog show to breed with a female dog; Peter and Lois try to convince Chris that "Arthur Valentine" doesn't exist.

title: Dog Bites Bear
plot: Stewie and Brian have a falling out; Peter refuses to wash his hand after meeting his favorite cereal mascot.

title: Send in Stewie, Please
plot: Stewie reveals secrets about himself in a session with his school psychologist.

title: V is for Mystery
plot: Stewie and Brian become detectives and embark on solving a string of murders set in Victorian era London.

title: Veteran Guy
plot: Peter and the guys get caught pretending to be military veterans and are sentenced to join the Coast Guard.

title: The Woof of Wall Street
plot: Brian convinces Stewie to teach him how to invest in the stock market; Peter and the guys look after the Drunken Clam while Jerome is away.

title: 'Family Guy' Through the Years
plot: The show looks back at the cultural events and issues that were tackled in the '50s, '60s and '70s.

title: Switch the Flip
plot: Chaos ensures in Quahog when Stewie's body swapping machine malfunctions.

title: HTTPete
plot: Peter adopts the millennial lifestyle, attracting the attention of a high-powered Silicon Valley executive.

title: The Unkindest Cut
plot: Quagmire has a freak accident; Stewie and Brian search for Mort after learning there is a $10,000 reward for turning him into the police.

title: Are You There God? It's Me, Peter
plot: After falling into a coma, Peter comes face-to-face with God, leading him to ask some of life's tough questions.
episode_title: Are You There God? It's Me, Peter

title: Married with Cancer
plot: Brian quickly falls in love with a woman, and after receiving devastating news regarding her cancer diagnosis, he proposes marriage.

title: Dead Dog Walking
plot: Brian's marriage to Jess doesn't go as planned, so at Peter's suggestion, he lets himself go, leading Jess to make a surprising decision.

title: Pal Stewie
plot: Stewie befriends a boy his age; Peter and Lois attend a seminar on self-empowerment.

title: Big Trouble in Little Quahog
plot: Stewie invents a shrinking machine that shrinks him and Brian down to microscopic size.

title: Regarding Carter
plot: Carter gives Lois a surprising birthday present that leads to an unfortunate accident, leaving him dependent on the Griffins' care.

title: Stand by Meg
plot: Stewie vows to make Meg's life better after she saves him from choking; Chris is sent to a vocational school.

title: The Griffin Winter Games
plot: Meg takes the family by surprise when she makes the US Winter Olympics team.

title: Con Heiress
plot: Stewie and Brian compete for the inheritance of a wealthy, older heiress; Peter and Chris battle for Mr. Herbert's affection.

title: Pawtucket Pete
plot: The Pawtucket Brewery hires new bosses, who decide to change the company's mascot, making Peter and Brian go head-to-head to become the new face.

title: Hefty Shades of Gray
plot: Tom Tucker teaches Peter the ways of reporting fake news; Brian and Stewie help Chris improve his love life.

title: Trump Guy
plot: The Griffins move to the White House where Peter is hired as the new Press Secretary.

title: Bri, Robot
plot: Brian worries about his legacy so Stewie makes a robot duplicate of him as a living biography

title: Trans-Fat
plot: Peter learns an important lesson when he's mistakenly identified as transgender.
